        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 10:41AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1041 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southwest of Springdale, moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Hindsville...                     Garfield...
Rogers...                         Beaver Lake...
Elkins...                         Tontitown...
Larue...                          Pea Ridge...
Cave Springs...                   Bentonville...
Avoca...                          Pleasant Ridge...
Gateway...                        Hobbs State Park...
Beaver...                         Best...
Rocky Comfort...                  Clifty...
Oak Hill...                       Busch...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 66 and 89.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for northwestern
Arkansas.</instruction>
